The '''Javan oriole''' ('''''Oriolus cruentus''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Oriolidae]].

It is found on [[Java]] in Indonesia where its natural [[habitat]]s are [[subtropical or tropical moist lowland forest]] and subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]].

[[Temuan people]] believe that its song brings bad luck.<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Binti Norazlimi |first1=Nor Atiqah |last2=Binti Mohd Sarif |first2=Amirah |date=2021-06-28 |title=Ethno-ornithology of Temuan Community in Ledang, Johor |journal=Journal of Sustainable Natural Resources |volume=02 |issue=1 |doi=10.30880/jsunr.2021.02.01.003 |issn=2716-7143|doi-access=free }}</ref>

